    "For example, shelves were used by participants to \"provide additional data [encodings]\" (P8) and code to \"have an exact way of defining [(genomics) coordinates]\" (P10).",
    "VbD was for basic annotations such as \"Adding a label\" and \"writing comments for sharing\".",
    "One participant (P2) mentioned a combination of 3 techniques to perform the task, using example+NLI+VbD, with examples to \"start in a certain style or with figure from another paper\", and to then \"adjust that style with NLI and VbD\" to arrange labels.",
    "Summarizing ElicitationsNone of the participants stuck to a single authoring technique across all tasks and noted that different authoring techniques accomplished different tasks.",
    "Participants reflected on the value of having flexibility in the system to be able to create expressive visualizations."
